overview: The user initiated a request for a complete aesthetic overhaul of
  their sleep questionnaire application, aiming to move beyond its current
  "okay" but generic appearance. I began by thoroughly reviewing the existing
  CSS and component files to understand the current design. Based on this
  analysis, I developed a strategy to implement a calming, sleep-themed visual
  language. This involved updating the global color palette to use deep indigos,
  purples, and teals, and introducing custom utility classes for gradients and
  shadows. Key components like the main questionnaire form, progress bar, intro
  section, and individual form fields (checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders) were
  redesigned for a more polished and cohesive look. All 14 form sections were
  updated to use consistent card-style groupings and theme-aligned colors,
  replacing the previous generic gray boxes. The report section also received
  significant styling improvements. The outcome is a visually transformed
  application that is professional, calming, and appropriate for a sleep health
  assessment, with all components and sections adhering to the new aesthetic
  guidelines.
